						<summary>

						<p>On a stone standing in a street at the western end of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Sarvajit, Adhika-Āshāḍha, śu. 7.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of land by Modalāri Nāyaka, the agent of Aṅkā-Jiyya to Maravāḷa Kōṭaya, son of Śivayōgi-Mallaya, on the occasion of his visit to the <hi rend="italic">tirtha (i.e., jatra)</hi> of the goddess of Paṭṭaṇam (<hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> Talamañchipaṭṭaṇam).</p>						

